Package fr.univparis.metro

Class Parser

java.lang.Object
fr.univparis.metro.Parser
public class Parser
extends Object
Tranform a file into a WGraph. The file must be in the following format:
  • A line starts with "Ligne number" where number is the number of the line and ends with --.
  • Then every station is linked to the next station and his predecessor (one station per line).
  • One sided cycle (as in line 10 of parisian subway) can be added by having a "{" line.
  • Then the station will only be linked to the next line of the File.
  • To indicate that the first branch of the cycle has ended insert a "\" line.
  • The next station will be the station that can end the cycle (link to the station before the begining of the cylce).
  • Write the station of the other branch knowing that every station will be linked to his predecessor in the file.
  • To end the cylce enter a "}" line
  • Double sided fork (as in line 7 of the parisian subway) can also be added, it should start with "[".
  • Then add all the station of the first branch.
  • To end the branch insert "||" in a line.
  • Then starts the other branch from the begining and add all the stations of that branch.
  • To end the fork insert a "]" line.
  • Note that a fork can't be in the middle of a line.
